sentences: Irving Fazola (December 10, 1912 – March 20, 1949) was an American jazz clarinetist.
After brief time with Glenn Miller and Gus Arnheim, Fazola became a member of the Bob Crosby band in 1938.
He achieved some fame with this band, ranking as top clarinetist in the DownBeat magazine polls of 1940 and 1941.
After leaving Crosby, he worked in bands in Chicago, New York, and New Orleans, including time with George Brunies at the Famous Door, before settling in New Orleans in 1943.
He died of a heart attack at the age of 36 in 1949.
Fazola influenced Fountain, whose style resembled Fazola's and who substituted for Fazola at the Opera House the night of his death.
